text: Liivi Sõrmus (born 17 February 1992) is an Estonian footballer who plays as a midfielder and has appeared for the Estonia women's national team. ==Career== Sõrmus has been capped for the Estonia national team, appearing for the team during the 2019 FIFA Women's World Cup qualifying cycle. In 2018, she moved from Pärnu JK to FC Kirkop United in Malta. ==References== ==External links== * * * Category:1992 births Category:Living people Category:Sportspeople from Pärnu Category:Estonian women's footballers Category:Estonia women's international footballers Category:Women's association football midfielders Category:Expatriate footballers in Malta Category:Estonian expatriate sportspeople in Malta Category:Estonian expatriate footballers
